Day 5: HTML Forms (Very Important 🔥)

Forms are used to collect user input in websites:

Login page
Registration page
Contact form
Search box

This is one of the MOST important topics for React + Spring Boot too.

1. Basic Form Structure
<form>
    <!-- form elements go here -->
</form>
2. Input Field
<input type="text">

Used to take text input.

Example:

Name: <input type="text">
3. Label (Very Important)

Used to describe input fields.

<label>Name</label>
<input type="text">
4. Common Input Types
Type	Purpose
text	Name, city
password	Hidden text
email	Email validation
number	Numbers only
date	Date picker

Examples:

<input type="text">
<input type="password">
<input type="email">
<input type="number">
<input type="date">
5. Password Field
<label>Password</label>
<input type="password">
6. Button
<button>Submit</button>

OR

<button type="submit">Login</button>
7. Textarea (Large Input)
<textarea rows="4" cols="30"></textarea>

Used for:

Comments
Address
Feedback
8. Select Dropdown
<select>
    <option>Java</option>
    <option>React</option>
    <option>Spring Boot</option>
</select>
9. Radio Buttons (Single Choice)
Gender:
<input type="radio" name="gender"> Male
<input type="radio" name="gender"> Female
10. Checkbox (Multiple Choice)
Skills:
<input type="checkbox"> Java
<input type="checkbox"> React
<input type="checkbox"> SQL
Mini Project: Registration Form
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Registration Form</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>User Registration</h1>

<form>

    <label>Name:</label><br>
    <input type="text"><br><br>

    <label>Email:</label><br>
    <input type="email"><br><br>

    <label>Password:</label><br>
    <input type="password"><br><br>

    <label>Date of Birth:</label><br>
    <input type="date"><br><br>

    <label>Gender:</label><br>
    <input type="radio" name="gender"> Male
    <input type="radio" name="gender"> Female<br><br>

    <label>Skills:</label><br>
    <input type="checkbox"> Java
    <input type="checkbox"> Spring Boot
    <input type="checkbox"> React<br><br>

    <label>Role:</label><br>
    <select>
        <option>Developer</option>
        <option>Tester</option>
        <option>DevOps</option>
    </select><br><br>

    <label>Address:</label><br>
    <textarea rows="4" cols="30"></textarea><br><br>

    <button type="submit">Register</button>

</form>

</body>
</html>
Important Concepts (Interview Focus)
1. Why do we use <form>?

To collect and submit user data to a server.

2. Difference between input types
text → normal text
password → hidden text
email → validates email format
3. Why do radio buttons use the same name?
<input type="radio" name="gender">

Because it allows only one selection.

4. Difference between checkbox and radio
Radio	Checkbox
Single selection	Multiple selection
Same name required	Independent selection
5. What is textarea?

Used for multi-line input like comments or address.
